lib/Topology/Algebra/MulAction.html#ContinuousSMul\">ContinuousSMul</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#IsTopologicalAddGroup\">IsTopologicalAddGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F'</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/MulAction.html#ContinuousSMul\">ContinuousSMul</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F'</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">→L[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F'</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distribution\">Distribution</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">→L[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distribution\">Distribution</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> <span class=\"fn\">F'</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Any continuous linear map `A : F →L[ℝ] G` induces a continuous linear map\n`𝓓'(Ω, F) →L[ℝ] 𝓓'(Ω, G)`. On locally integrable functions, this corresponds to applying `A`\npointwise. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distribution.mapCLM","kind":"def","line":179,"name":"Distribution.mapCLM","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.lean#L179-L183"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distributions.«term𝓓'(_,_)»\"><span class=\"name\">Distributions</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term𝓓'(_,_)»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We denote `𝓓'(Ω, F)` the space of `F`-valued distributions on `Ω`. Note that using `𝓓'`\nis a bit abusive since this is no longer a dual space unless `F = 𝕜`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distributions.«term𝓓'(_,_)»","kind":"def","line":166,"name":"Distributions.«term𝓓'(_,_)»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.lean#L166-L168"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Distributions.«term𝓓'^{_}(_,_)»\"><span class=\"name\">Distributions</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term𝓓'^{_}(_,_)»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We denote `𝓓'^{n}(Ω, F)` the space of `F`-valued distributions on `Ω` with order at most\n`n : ℕ∞`. Note that using `𝓓'` is a bit abusive since this is no longer a dual space unless\n`F = 𝕜`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Distribution/Distribution.html#Dis